answerText: El Nino [or El Nino/Southern Oscillation, or ENSO][10] During this warm year, Hurricane Mitch killed 11,000 in Central America. This year and the preceding year saw one of the most extreme El Nino events in modern history.

question: Question:  [10] Name this climatic phenomenon with a name referring to the Christ child, the warm phase of the Southern Oscillation which affects surface water off the west coast of South America.
